{"build_type":"executable","description":"LLM reader op.diff (content pin) with envelope. argv[1]=a pinned content hash the caller saw earlier (the 64-hex 'hash' op.read/op.map emit; optional), stdin=the current IPM package. Computes the package's current sha256 and compares it to the pin: equal -> {status:unchanged, hash} (the caller's cached copy is still valid; nothing is resent, which is the whole point); different -> {status:changed, hash, previous}; no pin given -> {status:new, hash}. Package-granular by design (matches op.read's whole-package hash) — flips if ANY function in the package changed; a sibling edit counts. Reuses compute_sha256_digest_into_buffer + format_digest_hex (the CAS hasher) and compare_two_strings_byte_by_byte (0 = equal). No document value graph duplication needed.","module_name":"compare-package-against-pinned-content-digest","package_name":"compare-package-against-pinned-content-digest","function_definitions":{"compare-package-against-pinned-content-digest":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"__argc","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"__argv","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"s_status","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"status"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"s_previous","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"previous"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"v_unchanged","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"unchanged"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"v_changed","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"changed"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"v_new","va